<html>
  <head>
    <title>UserData</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      Here, you can create new user data scripts to be used in the creation of instances. User data scripts are interpreted as ERB, which means that 
      ERB expressions are allowed. In particular, @instance is an object referring to the current instance which can be used inside the script.
    </p>
    <a href="/userdatas/new">Create a new user data script</a>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Actions</th>
      </tr>
      <% Userdata.all.each do |data| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= data.name %></td>
        <td><%= data.description %></td>
        <td><a href="/userdata/edit/<%= data.id %>">Edit</a> | <a href="/userdata/delete/<%= data.id %>">Delete</a> </td>
      </tr>
      <% end %>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>
  
